I'm writing this review solely to help out any fellow vegetarians who may go to this restaurant. While I appreciate that there is a veggie burger on the menu, don't get it. It's big and mushy, tastes like straight mashed up black beans and it's drowned in ranch. Completely not worth it. Get a salad without the meat instead. Our waiter was nice, and I'm sure they have better options for meat eaters but if you're vegetarian, steer clear of the veggie burger.

This was by far the worst restaurant/pub I have visited while exploring Chicago. I was promised a very nice scene, food, music, and drinks when I decided to head here. Outside of our hostess and her great hospitality, our experience quickly went downhill.  Our waiter was reluctant to ever visit our table. Waters weren't given until nearly 30-45 minutes of waiting. He completely forgot to give one of us our appetizers insisting that we said we didn't want it until everyone else had gotten their entree.  The food was anything but upscale pub food but still had upscale prices. The buffalo chicken dip was far inferior to any I've had at any other bar. There had to have been at least a 1cm deep layer of grease sloshing on top when it was put on our table. The chicken was chopped into big pieces making it hard to scoop up.  The bacon clam chowder was more of a clam broth with potatoes and bacon and was so watery and just bot very great tasting at all.  We waited an incredible amount of time for any service that should be standard. Our waiter was visibly off not working and talking to the hostess the entire time. I can't imagine coming back here unless I was in dire need of a drink. My Kentucky Mule is the best reason I can explain this having 2 stars and not 1.
